parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power steering can cause loss of control, accidents, and put the safety of the driver and passengers at risk, especially on high-speed roads or in hazardous weather conditions.
symptoms: The power steering fails
making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle
warning messages appear on the dashboard
such as "Steering: Malfunction! Please stop vehicle" or "Steering malfunction"
the steering wheel becomes hard to turn
especially at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning lane keeping assist system can cause distractions, loss of control, and accidents, especially on straight roads or during turns, and can be particularly dangerous if the system deactivates without warning.
symptoms: The lane keeping assist system issues false alerts
deactivates without warning
fails to detect driver attention
and can be extremely annoying and distracting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty emergency brake system can cause unexpected and sudden stops, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The emergency brake engages automatically while driving
the vehicle stops suddenly without warning
the brake system fails to operate
the vehicle becomes inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty tail light assembly can increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-visibility conditions, as other drivers may not be able to see the vehicle.
symptoms: The tail lights stop working suddenly
the backup and braking lights fail to operate
the license plate light is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning safety systems, such as airbag and pre-sense systems, can lead to false positives, unexpected braking, and confusion for the driver, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The passenger airbag turns on and off while driving
the safety system alert continues to occur while driving
the parking brake activates suddenly while reversing
the vehicle jerks or brakes suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: False Positives in Rear Cross Traffic Alert and Pre-Sense Systems
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: False positives in rear cross traffic alert and pre-sense systems can cause sudden and unexpected braking, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The system incorrectly senses an object and activates the parking brake
resulting in a sudden vehicle jerk
brakes scraping
and immediate confusion for the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger waste gate actuator can cause overboost conditions, leading to engine damage, loss of power, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Engine light on
faults stored for P334A00 and P023400
overboost condition
loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent false alerts from the lane assist system can be distracting and annoying, leading to drivers disabling the feature, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Frequent false alerts
alarm sounds while driving with hands on the wheel
feature becomes unusable.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Deceleration with Adaptive Cruise Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deceleration can cause accidents, especially at high speeds, and can lead to rear-end collisions.
symptoms: Sudden application of brakes
loss of speed
unexpected deceleration
adaptive cruise control setting changes without driver input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt release mechanism can cause difficulty or inability to release the seat belt, potentially leading to injuries or entrapment in emergency situations.
symptoms: The seat belt is difficult to release
the seat belt does not release
the seat belt requires excessive force to release.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Seat Lumbar Support Design Flaw
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the rear seat lumbar support can cause or exacerbate lower back injuries in the event of a rear-end collision, potentially leading to long-term back pain and discomfort.
symptoms: Lower back pain or injury
worsened back pain due to lumbar support design
lumbar support protrusion forced into lower lumbar region during collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Transmission Control Module (TCM) can cause the vehicle to suddenly jerk, slow down, and experience irregular gear shifting, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks abruptly
slows down to half the original speed
gear shifting becomes irregular
and the following indicators appear on the dashboard: check engine light
vehicle repair required
warning icon with triangle around and exclamation point
and "Drive system malfunction" note on the screen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended movement of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle moves forward unexpectedly
even when parked
and can crash into objects or other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slow down, or become stuck in a particular gear, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle displays a "catastrophic transmission failure" message
and the transmission shifts into manual third gear unexpectedly.
